TITLE: Creating and Executing Prepared SQL Statement in Mendix
DESCRIPTION: Java code for preparing and executing a SQL statement with parameters, then processing the results by creating Mendix objects for the returned dates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto9/extensibility/howto-datastorage-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
return (List<IMendixObject>) Core.dataStorage().executeWithConnection(connection -> {
    // Create and execute prepared statement
    PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(sql);
    statement.setDate(1, new java.sql.Date(startDate.getTime()));
    statement.setDate(2, new java.sql.Date(endDate.getTime()));
    statement.setDate(3, new java.sql.Date(startDate.getTime()));
    statement.setDate(4, new java.sql.Date(endDate.getTime()));
    ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery();

    // Process the results
    List<IMendixObject> results = new ArrayList<>();
    while (resultSet.next()) {
        FirstMondayDate mxObj = new FirstMondayDate(getContext());
        mxObj.setMondayDate(new Date(resultSet.getDate("monday").getTime()));
        results.add(mxObj.getMendixObject());
    }
    return results;
});
```

