TITLE: Implementing Property Validation for Sub-Objects in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example validation function that targets specific properties of sub-objects. This check function validates that the 'y' value of each data point is not greater than 10, returning appropriate error messages with specific property paths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/frontend/pluggable-widgets/pluggable-widgets-config-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function check(values) {
    var problems = [];
    values.dataPoints.forEach((p, i) => {
        if (p.y > 10) {
            problems.push({
                property: `dataPoints/${i + 1}/y`,
                message: "y should not be larger than 10"
            });
        }
    });
    return problems;
}
```

