TITLE: Creating a Data Loading Microflow for Knowledge Base Integration
DESCRIPTION: A microflow implementation that retrieves objects from a database, adds them to a chunk collection, and uploads them to a Mendix Cloud Knowledge Base. This process allows for grounding LLMs in application data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/appstore/use-content/platform-supported-content/modules/genai/how-to/ground_your_llm_in_data.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: microflow
CODE:
```
ACT_TicketList_LoadAllIntoKnowledgeBase
- Retrieve Objects (From database, MyFirstModule.Ticket, All, TicketList)
- Chunks: Initialize ChunkCollection (ChunkCollection)
- Loop over TicketList (For each item)
  - Chunks: Add KnowledgeBaseChunk to ChunkCollection ($ChunkCollection, $IteratorTicket/Description, empty, $IteratorTicket)
- Retrieve MxCloudKnowledgeBase (From database, MxGenAIConnector.MxCloudKnowledgeBase, First, MxCloudKnowledgeBase)
- Connection: Get (MxCloudKnowledgeBase, TicketSolutions, MxKnowledgeBaseConnection)
- Embed & Repopulate Collection (MxKnowledgeBaseConnection, GenAICommons.ChunkCollection, IsSuccess)
- Decision (Replace Success, Expression, $IsSuccess)
  - true: End event (return true)
  - false: End event (return false)
```

