TITLE: Rendering Expand/Collapse Icon (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet defines a `renderIcon` method in the display component (`GroupBox.tsx`) that renders either the `expandIcon` or `collapseIcon` based on the `collapsed` state. If the respective icon prop is not provided, it renders a default '+' or '-' sign.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto8/extensibility/build-native-widget.md#2025-04-21_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
private renderIcon = (): ReactNode => {
    const { collapseIcon, expandIcon } = this.props;

    if (this.state.collapsed) {
        return expandIcon ? expandIcon : <Text style={this.styles.headerContent}>+</Text>;
    }

    return collapseIcon ? collapseIcon : <Text style={this.styles.headerContent}>-</Text>;
};

```

