TITLE: Network Optimization Pseudocode
DESCRIPTION: Two optimization modes for data retrieval in Mendix: Network Round Trips returns all attributes and caches objects, while Network Load returns only required attributes without caching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide/runtime/datasource-runtime-behavior.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
// Network Round Trips Mode
fetch(orderLine) {
    return allAttributes        // Returns all entity attributes
    cacheObject(response)      // Caches complete object
    updateUI(immediately)      // Updates UI without reload
}

// Network Load Mode
fetch(orderLine) {
    return requestedAttributesOnly   // Returns only needed attributes
    skipCache()                     // Does not cache objects
    updateUI(onReload)              // Updates UI on data reload
}
```

