TITLE: Executing a Filtered SQL Query in Mendix with Snowflake
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet retrieves records from the HISTORY_DAY table with postal code and country filters to limit the dataset returned to the Mendix application. It enhances performance by allowing pre-filtering at the database level before data is displayed in the Mendix app. Parameters are expected to be provided dynamically based on user input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/appstore/use-content/platform-supported-content/modules/snowflake/snowflake-edc.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
select *
from   STANDARD_TILE.HISTORY_DAY
where  ({filterPostalCode1} IS NULL 
                or (postal_code like '%' ||{filterPostalCode2}|| '%'))
    and ({filterCountry1} IS NULL 
                or (country like '%' ||{filterCountry2}|| '%')) 
limit 1000
```

