TITLE: DynamicValue Type Definition in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the DynamicValue type which represents values that can change over time. It uses a discriminated union pattern with three possible states: Available, Unavailable, and Loading.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/frontend/pluggable-widgets/pluggable-parent-9/pluggable-widgets-client-apis-9/_index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export type DynamicValue<X> =
    | { readonly status: ValueStatus.Available; readonly value: X }
    | { readonly status: ValueStatus.Unavailable; readonly value: undefined }
    | { readonly status: ValueStatus.Loading; readonly value: X | undefined };

export const enum ValueStatus {
    Loading = "loading",
    Unavailable = "unavailable",
    Available = "available"
}
```

