TITLE: Implementing Pagination in a Mendix Widget using TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to implement pagination in a Mendix widget. It sets the initial limit in the constructor and provides methods to switch between pages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/frontend/pluggable-widgets/pluggable-parent-9/pluggable-widgets-client-apis-9/pluggable-widgets-client-apis-list-values-9.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
export default class PagedWidget extends Component<PagedWidgetProps> {
    constructor(props: PagedWidgetProps) {
        super(props);

        props.myDataSource.setLimit(props.pageSize);
    }
}

const ds = this.props.myDataSource;
const current = this.props.myDataSource.offset;
<button onClick={() => ds.setOffset(current - this.props.pageSize)}>
    Previous
</button>
<button onClick={() => ds.setOffset(current + this.props.pageSize)}>
    Next
</button>
```

