TITLE: Using StartsWith String Condition Helper in Mendix TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the startsWith helper to filter items where an attribute value begins with a specified substring. Works with String, Integer, Long, and Decimal attributes and String literals for both text and numeric comparisons.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/frontend/pluggable-widgets/pluggable-widgets-client-apis/pluggable-widgets-client-apis-list-values.md#2025-04-21_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const attrStr = attribute(this.props.myAttributeA.id); // string attribute
const subStr = literal("secret");

// filter keeps items where value starts with substring "secret"
// like "secret file", but not "my secret password" or "top secret"
