TITLE: Using Big.js for Numeric Precision in Mendix
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates using the Big.js library for high-precision arithmetic in JavaScript actions within Mendix.  Mendix represents decimal, integer, and long types as Big objects to avoid JavaScript's native number limitations. This example shows how to perform addition with Big.js.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto8/extensibility/best-practices-javascript-actions.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Precision limitation of JavaScript numbers
0.1 + 0.2                  // 0.30000000000000004
// Solved with BigJs
x = new Big(0.1)
y = x.plus(0.2)            // '0.3'
```

