TITLE: Jenkins HTTP Request with Groovy Script
DESCRIPTION: Groovy script example for Jenkins to make HTTP requests to Mendix APIs using the HTTP Request Plugin. Shows how to get the latest revision number for building deployment packages with credential binding.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto9/integration/implement-cicd-pipeline.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: groovy
CODE:
```
def get = new URL("https://deploy.mendix.com/api/1/apps/"+appId+"/branches/main").openConnection();
withCredentials([string(credentialsId: 'mendixUsername', variable: 'username'),
               string(credentialsId: 'mendixApiKey', variable: 'apikey')]) {
    def customHeaders = [[name: 'Mendix-Username', value: username],
                        [name: 'Mendix-ApiKey', value: apikey]]
    def response = httpRequest httpMode: 'GET',
                              url: "https://deploy.mendix.com/api/1/apps/"+appId+"/branches/main",
                              customHeaders: customHeaders
    def json = new groovy.json.JsonSlurper().parseText(response.content)
    return json.latestCommit.id
}
```

