TITLE: Summing Numeric Attribute Values in Object List
DESCRIPTION: This snippet sums attribute values within a list of Mendix objects. It ensures valid parameters by verifying the existence of an attribute name in the list objects and checking that it’s numeric. If conditions are not met, the snippet throws an error or returns zero for empty lists.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto9/extensibility/best-practices-javascript-actions.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function SumListAttributeValues(objectList, attributeName) {
    if (!attributeName || attributeName.trim() === "") {
        throw new Error("The 'Attribute name' parameter can not be empty");
    }
    if (!objectList || objectList.length === 0) {
        return new Big(0);
    }
    if (!objectList[0].has(attributeName)) {
        throw new Error("List of type " + objectList[0].getEntity() + " does not have an attribute named " + attributeName);
    }
    if (!objectList[0].isNumeric(attributeName)) {
        throw new Error("List of type " + objectList[0].getEntity() + " an attribute named " + attributeName + " is not numeric");
    }
    /* implementation */
}
```

