TITLE: Implementing Extended CASE Expression in SQL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases the use of an extended CASE expression that evaluates price thresholds to classify order types. It returns 'Priority' if the price is above 7, 'Lucky' if the number is 7, and 'Regular' otherwise. This functionality is implemented in a SQL SELECT query on the Sales.Order table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide/modeling/domain-model/oql/oql-expression-syntax.md#2025-04-21_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT
	LastName,
	Number,
	Price,
	CASE
		WHEN Price > 7 THEN 'Priority'
		WHEN Number = 7 THEN 'Lucky'
		ELSE 'Regular'
		END AS OrderType
FROM Sales.Order
```

