TITLE: Disable Large Send Offload (IPv4) in Parallels Network Adapter (Windows)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet guides users to disable the Large Send Offload (IPv4) setting in the Parallels VirtIO Ethernet Adapter properties within Windows Device Manager. This can potentially improve network upload speed issues experienced when using Parallels with Mendix Studio Pro.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto8/general/using-mendix-studio-pro-on-a-mac.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
"1. In Windows 10/11, navigate to **Start** > **Control Panel**> **Device Manager** > **Network adapters** > **Parallels VirtIO Ethernet Adapter**.

2. Right-click **Parallels VirtIO Ethernet Adapter** and select **Properties** in the drop-down list. 
3. On the **Advance** tab, find the **Large Send Offload** **(IPv4)** property and change its value to **Disabled**. 
4. Click **OK**."
```

