TITLE: Exporting Data from Mendix Environment to a Backup File
DESCRIPTION: Shell commands for exporting data from a Mendix environment to a backup file. The commands create necessary resources, copy the data migration tool to the pod, execute the backup process, and copy the resulting backup file to the local machine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/deployment/private-cloud/private-cloud-data-transfer.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
NAMESPACE={namespace}
ENVIRONMENT={environment}
# Create the resources required for the backup operation
kubectl -n $NAMESPACE apply -f /tmp/mendix-backup-restore.yaml
# Copy the Linux version of the data migration tool into the Pod
kubectl -n $NAMESPACE cp mxpc-data-migration mendix-backup-restore:/tmp/mxpc-data-migration
# Run the backup process
