TITLE: Implementing ResNet50 Pre-processor in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of image pre-processing for ResNet50 model including OpenCV initialization, image resizing, normalization and conversion to base64 format. Requires OpenCV library and handles 224x224 image dimensions with specific normalization parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide9/modeling/integration/machine-learning-kit/design-patterns/pre-post-processor-patterns.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
static {
  nu.pattern.OpenCV.loadShared(); //OpenCV initialization
}

@java.lang.Override
public IMendixObject executeAction() throws Exception
{
  this.RawImage = this.__RawImage == null ? null : resnet50.proxies.ResNet.initialize(getContext(), __RawImage);

  // BEGIN USER CODE
  ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
  this.RawImage.getContents(getContext(), bos);
  byte[] binaryImage = bos.toByteArray();
  Mat img = Imgcodecs.imdecode(new MatOfByte(binaryImage), Imgcodecs.IMREAD_COLOR);

  // 1. resize image
  Mat rim = new Mat();
  Size sz = new Size(224, 224);
  Imgproc.resize(img, rim, sz);

  // 2. normalize image
  float[] mean = new float[] {0.485f, 0.456f, 0.406f};
  float[] std = new float[] {0.229f, 0.224f, 0.225f};
  float[][][][] inputArray = new float[1][3][224][224];
  for(int i = 0; i < 224; i++) {
    for(int j = 0; j < 224; j++) {
      for(int k = 0; k <= 2; k++) {
        double[] rawValue = rim.get(i, j);
        float normalizedValue = (((float) (rawValue[Math.abs(k - 2)] / 255) - mean[k]) / std[k]);
        inputArray[0][k][i][j] = normalizedValue;
      }
    }
  }    
  InputStream is = MLKit.toInputStream(inputArray);
  String base64 = MLKit.toBase64(is);
  IMendixObject outputObject = Core.instantiate(getContext(), "ResNet50.ML_Input_Entity_ResNet50ModelMapping");
  outputObject.setValue(getContext(), "Data", base64);
  return outputObject;
}
```

