TITLE: Using EndsWith String Condition Helper in Mendix TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the endsWith helper to filter items where an attribute value ends with a specified substring. Works with String, Integer, Long, and Decimal attributes and String literals for both text and numeric comparisons.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/frontend/pluggable-widgets/pluggable-widgets-client-apis/pluggable-widgets-client-apis-list-values.md#2025-04-21_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const attrStr = attribute(this.props.myAttributeA.id); // string attribute
const subStr = literal("secret");

// filter keeps items where value ends with substring "secret"
// like "top secret", but not "my secret password" or "secret file"
const filterCondition1 = startsWith(attrStr, subStr);

// also works with numeric attributes
const attrNum = attribute(this.props.myAttributeB.id); // integer attribute
const subNum = literal("1337");

// filter keeps items where value ends with sequence of numbers "1337"
// like "1231337", but not "133700" or "913379"
const filterCondition2 = startsWith(attrNum, substrNum);
```

