TITLE: Creating Entity and Attribute with Model API in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to add a new entity with an attribute to the Mendix model. It creates a transaction, instantiates entity and attribute objects, sets their names, adds the attribute to the entity, and then commits the transaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/apidocs-mxsdk/apidocs/studio-pro/extensibility-api/csharp/extensibility-api-howtos/interact-with-model-api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using (var transaction = model.StartTransaction("add entity"))
{
    var entity = CurrentApp.Create<IEntity>();
    var attr = CurrentApp.Create<IAttribute>();
    entity.Name = "testEntity";
    attr.Name = "testAttribute";
    entity.AddAttribute(attr);
    var copyEntity = CurrentApp.Copy(entity);
    transaction.Commit();
}
```

