TITLE: Adjusting renderIcon Method with Styles (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet updates the `renderIcon` method in the container component (`GroupBox.tsx`) to apply the correct color and size to the `Icon` component. It retrieves the color and size values from the `styles` attribute, which is the result of merging the default styles and custom styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/howto8/extensibility/build-native-widget.md#2025-04-21_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
private renderIcon = (toBeRenderedIcon: DynamicValue<NativeIcon> | undefined, glyph: string) => {
    const nativeIcon: NativeIcon = 
        toBeRenderedIcon && toBeRenderedIcon.status === ValueStatus.Available
            ? toBeRenderedIcon.value
            : { type: "glyph", iconClass: glyph };

    return (
        <Icon color={this.styles.headerContent.color} icon={nativeIcon} size={this.styles.headerContent.fontSize} />
    );
};

```

