TITLE: Connecting to Azure SQL Database via Shell
DESCRIPTION: This shell command retrieves an access token for Azure SQL Database, then connects to the database using the `sqlcmd` client with the retrieved token. It also removes the temporary token file after use.  The <hostname> placeholder needs to be replaced with the actual server name.
