TITLE: Group by Clause Example - Conditional Grouping
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query illustrates the GROUP BY clause with a HAVING constraint, returning summed order prices per city only for those cities where the total is greater than 1000.00 or the city name is Losdun.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide9/modeling/resources/data-sets/oql/oql-group-by-clause.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT SUM(Sales."Order"/TotalPrice)
FROM Sales."Order"
INNER JOIN Sales."Order"/Sales.Customer_Order/Sales.Customer/Sales.Customer_Address/Sales.Address
GROUP BY Sales.Address/City
HAVING SUM(Sales."Order"/TotalPrice) > 1000.0 OR Sales.Address/City = 'Losdun'
```

