TITLE: Using Subquery with EXISTS in HAVING Clause in SQL
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use a subquery with the EXISTS operator in the HAVING clause. This example groups locations by city and finds cities that have at least one Rekall brand location.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide/modeling/domain-model/oql/oql-clauses.md#2025-04-21_snippet_61

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT COUNT(*) AS LocationCount, City AS City
FROM Sales.Location AS Location
GROUP BY City
HAVING
	EXISTS (
		SELECT *
		FROM Sales.Location AS SubLocation
		WHERE
			Location/City = SubLocation/City
			AND SubLocation/Brand = 'Rekall'
	)
```

