TITLE: Using Subquery as a Value in WHERE Clause in SQL
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use a subquery as a value in the WHERE clause. The subquery must return exactly one column and at most one row. This example finds locations with maximum stock in each city.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mendix/docs/blob/development/content/en/docs/refguide/modeling/domain-model/oql/oql-clauses.md#2025-04-21_snippet_57

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT Brand, City
FROM Sales.Location AS Location
WHERE
	Location.Stock = (
		SELECT MAX(Stock)
		FROM Sales.Location AS MaxStockLocation
		WHERE Location.City = MaxStockLocation.City
	)
```

